%p
  %b Cut and paste the following code and add to the post:

%p There are two sizes for thumbnails: (:thumb) and (:medium)

%p Smaller thumbnail (i.e., for front page):

= "![](#{@photo.file.url(:thumb)})"

%p Larger thumbnail (i.e., for posts):

= "![](#{@photo.file.url(:medium)})"


%br

%p To float the picture to the right:

= "![](#{@photo.file.url(:medium)}):right"

%br

%p To display the thumbnail and link to the full photo:
%p
  %em Replace the "put caption here" with photo caption.

&lt;a href=&quot;#{@photo.file.url}&quot; rel=&quot;lightbox&quot; title=&quot;put caption here&quot; &gt; &lt;img src=&quot;#{@photo.file.url(:medium)}&quot; />&lt;/a&gt;

%br

%p To float the thumbnail to the right and link to the full photo:

&lt;a href=&quot;#{@photo.file.url}&quot; rel=&quot;lightbox&quot; title=&quot;put caption here&quot; style=&quot;float:right;&quot; &gt;&lt;img src=&quot;#{@photo.file.url(:medium)}&quot; />&lt;/a&gt;

%br
%p Replace "medium" with "thumb" in the links above to use the smaller thumbnail.
%br

= link_to_function content_tag(:small, "[ CLOSE ]", :style => "float:right;"), "Effect.Fade('photolinks', { duration: 0 } )"
